#1) Download the data and check the MD5 checksum of a file run md5sum myFile.
wget --user XY-Z01-F001 --password XY URL 
#for each txt, md5 and tar file

#In the txt or MD5 file, you should see a check sum. When using "cksum FILE", it will create a string of numbers and letters, which if identical with the number in the MD5 file, shows data integrity. 
cksum FILE
#string appears

#2) Back-up at ALLAS
#Connect to Allas from CSC puhti, foollow tutorial:
https://docs.csc.fi/data/Allas/using_allas/a_commands/

#First, load allas module
module load allas

#Configure project
allas-conf project_2009316
#Note: it takes a moment or two

#From the scratch folder where data is stored, run the code below to uploads data
a-put FILE -b YOUR_RAW_DATA_BUCKET
# "-b" specifies a "bucket", a folder in which the data is stored and then the name of this

#To access data on Allas, you need to load allas module
module load allas

#Then configure to get access by doing
allas-conf YOUR_PROJECT

#Then, call lust of files using the project folder
a-list YOUR_RAW_DATA_BUCKET

#To download data from ALLAS, use, e.g.
a-get YOUR_RAW_DATA_BUCKET/dataset_3.tar


#3) Now, we extract files and delete tar files
#Extract files from tar using
tar -xavf Individual_files.tar.gz

#-x --> extract
#-a --> automatically detecs the compression format and to decompress it
#-v --> verbose -displays output
#-f --> tells which tar exactly
